        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         they can't add dot-stacking to the game.. it would make things far too easy.. and just doesn't really make sense to begin with.</P><P>if they made it so two necros casting the same dot does twice the dmg, then wouldn't they also have to make it so two shammies casting regen on a tank causes twice the regen? dots are debuffs.. and no spells that have a duration (whether they're buffs, debuffs, or whatever) stack, it just doesn't make sense for them to stack.. </P><P>if they gave this to necros (or any dot-casting class for that matter) then they'd have to make clerics be able to stack as many aego's as they want to, and make chanters stack as many tash's as they want onto a mob, etc etc etc..</P><P>heh and even aside from all that.. how would it make sense for necro#1's splurt to stack with necro#2's splurt.. yet if necro#1 just casts it twice, it doesn't stack on itsself?</P><P>**Dotcha Tilludie** <BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
