        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         DotchaSZ - Dots are NOT debuffs... some of them have a debuff component, but the very meaning of DoT is DAMAGE over Time.  They are not the same as buffs, nor would the same rules have to apply.  I don't think you'll find anyone that would advocate things like Aego and Chloro stacking on a single tank just because different casters casted it, that would be idiotically unbalancing.  What it boils down to is that DoTs are the primary form of damage that Necros have at their disposal, it's an inherent ability to the class, and the most efficient way that we have to deal damage and take down targets.  We know that when we started the class, it's there from the beginning and we just get more and more powerful ones as we move up.  </P><P>Melees have one way to deal damage and that is to whack the target with their swords, bows, fists, feet, or whatever other "tool" they happen to have... all of them can hit at the same time with no real limitations (other than lag, proximity to target, and other semantics).  </P><P>DD casters also have a primary damage form, that being the "nuke", basically any direct damage spell that inflicts instant damage to the target... again, there is no practical limitation on how many of them can hit the target at any given time.  They can chain-cast their spells as long as their mana lasts and never will they be blocked or have their efficiency reduced by another DD caster casting the same spells.</P><P>The only problem is that DoT stacking does not currently work, so while the melee and dd-casters can gang up on the mob the necros either have to cast completely different lines of DoT spells, split up the few good DoTs that a single necro could have done by himself, or result to the few highly inefficient small-damage DDs that we get or use severely-inefficient lifetaps.  And even then those alternate lines are frequently resisted.  DoT stacking is really just a way to make multiple necros viable in large-target situations, currently the system is assinine and allows for stacking of all other classes except those who use DoTs as their primary damage... namely Necros, and perhaps Shamans slightly, though they tend to have enough responsibilities on raids, and maybe rogue's poisons (they're essentially DoTs right?).</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=235322" target="_blank">Zetapsi Kappaphi</a> - 57 Dark-elf Necromonster <BR>The Watchmen of Karana<BR><a href="http://www.betawatcher.com/" target="_blank">Betawatcher.com - Shape your world!</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
