         DotchaSZ, first off, I agree with you that a single necro stacking the same DoT on a mob multiple times would be unbalancing.  I'm sure that was the primary intent.  That a single necro can act in the manner he could if he was solo.  If a single necro casts a DoT on a mob, then casts the same one again before it runs out, the timer gets reset.  The intent is for multiple necros to be able to do this on the same mob, without conflicting with others.</P><P>As far as your argument dealing with shamans/druids/rangers all stacking regens, I would also have to agree that that would be unbalancing.  I think all of us would agree with that.  I'm sure there will be special provisions taken to prevent this, such as maybe only allowing things to stack only if damage is done?</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=191272" target="_blank">Merkurion Everdeth</a><BR>=--60 Warlock of The Rathe--=<BR>Member of <a href="http://66.205.128.39/" target="_blank">Tindi' Losi</a></P><P>"Get busy living, or get busy dying" -The Shawshank Redemption<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
