         Ali, I know for a fact NDS broke and HELD fear open.  I think it lasted 3 days before they got bored (I would imagine shifts like at work).  This was on Tarew Marr Server.</P><P>Dot Stacking would not trivialize any encounters.  I watched a group take Gore out in about 30 secs last weekend.  I didn't even have time to get a cast off to get some of the faction.  Group was 2 wizzies, a necro, and prolly a monkie puller, but not sure.  All I noticed.  Zrazzt could tell you better about what was there.</P><P>DoT stacking would merely make it so necros wouldn't have to figure out before hand what who is going to cast, and make the possibility of more than 3 necros in hate/fear/etc... a possibility.  As it is, I know for the most part I am on most raids as a shit we got wiped, send in the lizard to get us going again contingient, and not for damage.  Typically, I don't have need to twitch unless we don't have at least one battle cleric with us.</P><P>Lets use easy to get spells as an example.  Splirt and Envenomed Bolt.  Not too hard to get to 51, and is easily buyable.  3 necros splirt and ebolt an Amy Warrior (just an example),  Ebolt will do 1020 damage in about 45 secs (*3=3060 damage) and Splirt will do 1600 damage in 1 min 45 (*3=4800 damage).  Meaning the 3 necros did 7860 damage in a little less than 2 min (add casting times and recast times in to get to about 2 min.  We can't chain cast like the npc's).</P><P>While this example does assume nothing from a resist (Amy Warriors aren't that tough anyways), it shows us doing a decient damage (with the pet you are doing more, add about another 1k damage from all three pets over that time.  estimate conservative imho).  This makes a necro a more viable place on a raid.  Your not just a corpse summoner/twitch bitch/ghetto mezzer/FD rezzer (55+).  You can now do your damage potential, allowing for smoother raids.</P><P>Using the same above example without dot stacking, you get one necro casting ebolt for 1020 damage, one casting Splirt for 1600, and one having to use Ignite blood for 1200.  Using the same 2 min scenario ( i know ignite is a little over 2 min), you have 3820 damage plus 1k from pets making 4820.  Same number of necros using same ammount of pets doing about half as much damage.</P><P>Mana quantities spent is negociable from Lich or the breeze/clarity lines of spells.</P><P>This is just an example on a relatively easy creature that is relatively easy to find/kill.  Now put that same scenario on 3 51 necros on a vox/naggy raid, hole, chardok, velious or Luclin and add us being able to throw a few nukes in as well, and Lich/C3 stacking and you have necros being well balanced with the other caster classes.</P><P>One last thing, we were always a threat to the "holy trinity" of cleric/warrior/chanter.  That's why we were raped by the nerf dick.  At least my scaled arse chaffed it bad when I was raped.</P><P>edit: had to add the last smart ass remark.</P><P>Death takes on many faces, yours takes on mine.<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=311916" target="_blank">Lizalfos Deathscale</a><BR><a href="http://www.guildportal.com/Guild.asp?GuildID=1637&TabID=594" target="_blank">Blood Red Rose</a></P><P>Edited by - Lizalfos on 08/01/2002  12:24:31<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
