         Yes, I'm a supporter of necro_01 and necro_02's dot's taking the same buff slot. </P><P>Here is why- wizzy_01 casts Garrison's Superior Sundering(2100) on mob, wizzy_02 casts same dd on mob, wizzy_03 casts same dd on mob. This is their primary dmg form. DD's stack because their effect is instant. 5 wizzies can do 10,500 dmg instantly to mob_01.(after the 8 sec cast time) compare this to necros. </P><P>Necro_01 casts FP(2160 over 54 sec...if a nec is lucky enough to get this spell), vexing (1048 over 54 sec), CoC (1000 over 60 sec), Plauge (60dd +1155 over 126 sec), Splurt (1600 over 96 sec). Necro_02- necro_05 does the same. Aprox 102.4dps once they're all stacked per necro. 512dps with 5 necros stacking. So, in 8 seconds (after all the dot's have been applied) the 5 necros would have done 4096 dmg. Now then, it has taken us 26.1 seconds to cast all these spells. oops, that's casting time alone. We'd need to FD off the agro between each casting and stagger it out so that main tank keeps the agro. </P><P>Averaged out for casting times, ammount of time to do the stacking, etc... in one minute 5 necros would do less than 25k dmg. </P><P>The wizzies? including recast times and casting times and allowing for agro management, etc...About 42k. (assuming only casted 4 nukes each instead of the max of 7 per minute. even if they only casted 2 each they'd still be close in dmg. )</P><P>how would necro dot stacking be unbalancing. Do you see 4 warlocks being able to go dot a dragon(old world) to death? I sure don't. At least not without them all getting killed. </P><P>Bah, Time for the mid-day meeting. Check my math, if I'm wrong then let me know. I don't want wizzies nerfed at all. Don't take my comparisons to mean that. I'm just trying to show how dot stacking would not be unbalancing. It would just give extra necros a purpose to attend raids without being a mana bitch.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264137" target="_blank" target="_bla