         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>they can't add dot-stacking to the game.. it would make things far too easy.. and just doesn't really make sense to begin with.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>The only thing that could stop VI from adding it is the game engine.  Once all the possible exploits are covered DoT stacking should be added to EQ.  It will not have such a huge impact upon EQ as 4 manaburning Wizards killing Kurnak dragons.</P><P>And to an extent it does make sense.  For example:  If you are bitten by a Rattle snake you will be in some pain but you will live.  Now what if you fell into a den of them and were bitten several times?  </P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>DOTs are not regen debuffs. Disease dot's have a regen debuff, but last i checked the others do not. The do a specific ammount of dmg per tick. BIG difference. Before calling other people's comments stupid why not take a look at what you say?<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>No, your missing his point.  The only real difference between a DoT and a Regen spell is a DoT has a negative HP modifier while a Regen has a positive one.  They are essentially just the opposite sides of a coin.</P><P>Now VI does have the ability to define them as different, they added the determental type to all DoTs when they created Focus items.  Thus it would be easy for VI to code DoT stacking and disallow all others.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>uh, ever been on a raid with 2 epic enchanters? did ya want a 3rd?<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Completely different classes and different roles.  Enchanters have more then enough to do with debuffing, buffing and CC during raids.  Not to mention semi decent DD ability (arguely better then our own).  And yes I have been upon raids where I wished we had another chanter, the HP and the Emp are fine examples.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote><BR>my point is, why should they? the only real reason anyone has come up with so far is that necros get bored when there's more than 2 present on a boss-mob raid<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Because when VI designed the Necromancer they made us highly dependent upon DoTs.  As the game grew that dependency has become a limitaion, one I would bet they never intended.  It is a design flaw with the class that should never have existed.</P><P>Bril</P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
